cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Age of Information (AoI) and derives bounds on expected weighted sum AoI of users in broadcast networks with feedback. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper studies broadcast networks with feedback and considers coding actions to improve AoI. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper devises randomized and deterministic policies for coding actions in broadcast networks. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper considers randomized policies for coding actions. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with multiple users in broadcast networks and derives bounds on expected weighted sum AoI.
